<p>
  To get a better understanding of the purpose of the measures and how it
  addresses pressures, including pressures not identified under Article 8<em
    >(1)</em
  >
  on different parts of the ecosystem, the assessor should check the scheme
  fields: &lsquo;MeasureDescription&rsquo; (free text) and
  &lsquo;MeasurePurpose&rsquo; where the MS is required to specify whether the
  measure:
</p>
<p><br /></p>
<ul>
  <ul>
    <ul>
      <ul>
        <ul>
          <ol type="a">
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                Directly
                <strong>prevent further inputs of pressure</strong> (e.g. by
                managing the source activity)
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                Directly
                <strong>reduce existing levels of the pressure</strong> in the
                marine environment (e.g. removal of litter or oil spill
                clean-up)
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                Indirectly
                <strong>prevent further inputs of pressure</strong> (e.g. by
                governance mechanisms, financial incentives, awareness
                campaigns)
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                Directly<strong> restores</strong> a species or habitat(s)23
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                Ad-hoc measure for an exception under Art. 14(1) (b), (c) or (d)
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                <em
                  >Improve knowledge base (e.g. by research or one-off
                  surveys)</em
                >
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                <em
                  >Establish monitoring programmes (of relevant activities,
                  pressures or impacts)</em
                >
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE">
                <em
                  >Assess effectiveness of the measures (through assessing
                  changes in state/impact/pressure in the marine
                  environment)</em
                >
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p lang="fr-BE"><em>Not known</em></p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </ul>
      </ul>
    </ul>
  </ul>
</ul>
<p><br /></p>
<p>
  Note that, according to the definition in GD10, options f, g and h do not fall
  within the definition of measures, but if reported in the PoM update (e.g.
  because they were also reported in the first cycle), they should be classified
  here. These categories should only be used when they are the main focus of the
  reported &lsquo;measure&rsquo; (i.e. not if they are a component of a measure
  focused on categories a-e).
</p>
<p><br /></p>
<p>
  In addition, the assessor should check the text report to verify whether any
  supporting information justifies how the different pressures are addressed by
  the modified new measures and the additional new measures in the second cycle,
  i.e. assess whether the measures address all reported activities.
</p>
